    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1876-05-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1876-05-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="170"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d170">
                <head>No. 160.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Edward Thornton</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Fish</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1876-05-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 23, 1876</date>. (Received May
                        23.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In compliance with a request which I have
                    received from the Governor-General of Canada, I have the honor to inform you
                    that two men, named Walter Moore and Frederick Moore, charged with the crime <pb
                        facs="0364" n="308" xml:id="pg_308"/> of murder in Canada, are fugitives
                    from justice, and are now under arrest in Boston, having been remanded till
                    to-morrow, and to ask that, when the necessary forms shall have been complied
                    with to your satisfaction, a warrant may be issued for their extradition, and
                    for their delivery to Alphonse Cinq, who is authorized to receive the
                    prisoners.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>EDW’D THORNTON.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
